lead_paragraph: The financial implications the Rugby Football Union could suffer for moving England matches away from Twickenham to raise the sport's profile in the country outweighs the potential benefits of northern tests, RFU chairman Andy Cosslett has said.

headline.print_headline: RFU Not Planning to Move England Games From Twickenham
headline.main: RFU Not Planning to Move England Games From Twickenham
